  "text": "The trait method candidate collection and ambiguous error reporting in rust-lang/rust is implemented across three primary files:\n\n## Candidate Collection (compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/probe.rs)\n\nThe `probe.rs` file contains the core logic for collecting trait method candidates. The `ProbeContext` struct manages the collection process through several key methods:\n\n1. **Inherent Candidate Assembly** (`assemble_inherent_candidates`, line 802): Iterates through receiver types and collects inherent impl methods.\n\n2. **Trait Candidate Assembly** (`assemble_extension_candidates_for_traits_in_scope`, line 1054): Collects trait methods from traits in the current scope by iterating through trait bounds and supertraits.\n\n3. **Comprehensive Trait Search** (`assemble_extension_candidates_for_all_traits`, line 1109): Assembles candidates from all available traits when doing diagnostic searches.\n\n4. **Candidate Evaluation** (`consider_candidates`, line 1676): The critical function that filters candidates and detects ambiguity. It:\n   - Maps candidates to their match status\n   - Filters out unstable candidates when appropriate\n   - Attempts to collapse multiple trait candidates to a single choice via `collapse_candidates_to_trait_pick` (line 2263) and `collapse_candidates_to_subtrait_pick` (line 2297)\n   - Returns `MethodError::Ambiguity` when multiple candidates remain after collapsing (line 1741)\n\n## Ambiguity Error Reporting (compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/suggest.rs)\n\nThe `suggest.rs` file handles the user-facing error messages. The `report_method_error` function (line 185) routes different `MethodError` variants, including `MethodError::Ambiguity` (line 221), which:\n\n1. Creates error code E0034 \"multiple applicable items in scope\" (line 225-226)\n2. Calls `note_candidates_on_method_error` (line 233-242) to annotate each candidate with its source location and container trait/impl\n3. Generates suggestions for using fully-qualified syntax to disambiguate\n\n## Return Type Notation Handling (compiler/rustc_hir_analysis/src/hir_ty_lowering/bounds.rs)\n\nThe `lower_return_type_notation_ty` function (line 796) handles the lowering of return type notation (RTN) bounds used in trait method specifications. This is relevant to ICE issues like #139387 where ambiguous trait methods with RTN syntax can cause panics during candidate collection and evaluation.\n\nThe call chain flows: `pick` → `pick_all_method` → `pick_method` → `consider_candidates` → ambiguity detection and `report_method_error` in suggest.rs."
